-- Anglo, Coal of Africa and Conduit: South African Stocks Preview
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a   a n d   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-11-05T05:53:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/bhp-billiton-coal-of-africa-south-african-equities-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  gained
509.93, or 1.7 percent, to 31,327.90 at the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg, the highest level since June 2008.  Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): Workers at Anglo American and
Xstrata Plc’s Collahuasi copper mine in northern Chile will
strike from today after wage negotiations with the company ended
without an agreement, Jacqueline Cerda, a union leader, said.
Shares of Anglo, owner of stakes in some of the world’s largest
diamond and platinum mines, added 6.86 rand, or 2.1 percent, to
330.01 rand.  BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ): The world’s largest mining
company will face a protest march over pay at its aluminum
smelters in Richards Bay, South Africa, the National Union of
Metalworkers of South Africa said.  BHP may also resort to share buybacks or bid for Anadarko
Petroleum Ltd. and Woodside Petroleum Ltd. after its $40 billion
offer for Potash Corp. of Saskatchewan Inc. was blocked by
Canada, UBS AG said. Shares in BHP rose 15.50 rand, or 6.2
percent, to 267.50 rand.  Coal of Africa Ltd.  (CZA SJ): The miner’s Mooiplaats
colliery will comply with South African environmental
regulations “in time,” said Chief Executive Officer  John Wallington . Closing the mine would result in 500 job losses, he
said. Shares of the company advanced 25 cents, or 3.1 percent,
to 8.25 rand.  Conduit Capital Ltd.  (CND SJ): The investment holding
company said it expects earnings per share for the year through
August to be 4.55 cents, down from 6.29 cents a year earlier, it
said in a statement. Shares in Conduit fell 2 cents, or 3.5
percent, to 56 cents.  Shares or American depositary receipts of South African
companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) jumped 3.6 percent to $24.14.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) gained 5.5 percent to $49.17. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) advanced 6.8 percent to $79.02. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) climbed 6.3 percent to $5.05. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) added 7.3 percent to $16.77. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) rose 8.3 percent to $12.36. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) increased 6.4 percent to $30.10. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
gained 0.6 percent to $4.91. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) added 2.4
percent to $47.98.  To contact the reporter on this story:
